> 
> 1. The Joint Program on the Science and Policy of Global Change: This is a collaborative effort between the MIT Energy Initiative and the Center for Global Change Science. The program's research focuses on the economic and policy aspects of climate change, including the costs and benefits of different policy options.
> 
> 2. The MIT Environmental Solutions Initiative: This initiative brings together researchers from across MIT to work on pressing environmental challenges, including climate change. Its research focuses on developing technological and policy solutions that can help mitigate the impacts of climate change.
> 
> 3. The MIT Center for Energy and Environmental Policy Research: This research center focuses on the economics and policy of energy and the environment. Its researchers work on a range of issues related to climate change, including the costs and benefits of different policy approaches.
> 
> 4. The MIT Joint Program on the Science and Policy of Global Change, MIT Environmental Solutions Initiative, and MIT Center for Energy and Environmental Policy Research have collaborated on the MIT Climate Portal. The Climate Portal is a platform that brings together the latest research on climate change, including information on its socioeconomic impacts.
> 
> These are just a few examples of the many researchers and groups at MIT who are working on the socioeconomic risks of climate change.
